  05 Mar 2007; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  x86/installcd-2.6.19.config, x86/livecd-2.6.19.config:
  Added SATA support back into the x86 configs.

  12 Feb 2007; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  -x86/installcd-2.6.17.config, -x86/livecd-2.6.17.config,
  +x86/installcd-2.6.19.config, +x86/livecd-2.6.19.config:
  Added new 2.6.19-friendly kernel configs. These should also resolve a few
  open bugs against the kernel configs for the release.

  23 Oct 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  x86/livecd-2.6.17.config:
  Added lm_sensors support via modules.

  23 Oct 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  amd64/livecd-2.6.17.config:
  Updated kernel config to 2.6.17-gentoo-r7.

  20 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  x86/livecd-2.6.17.config:
  Added AGPGART support to the LiveCD kernel for x86.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  -sparc/sparc64/2.6.16-sparc64-generic.config,
  +sparc/sparc64/installcd-2.6.17.config,
  -sparc/sparc64/2.6.17-sparc64-generic.config:
  Renamed the sparc kernel config file to match our naming conventions and
  removed the unused config.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.17-G5.config:
  Changed CONFIG_IEEE1394_ETH1394=y to CONFIG_IEEE1394_ETH1394=m.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  hppa/installcd-2.6.16-hppa32.config, hppa/installcd-2.6.16-hppa64.config:
  Turn off SCSI tape support on a non-LiveCD build, since we don't have any
  tools anyway on the InstallCD.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  -ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.15-G5.config,
  -ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.15-power.config, +alpha/livecd-2.6.16.19.config,
  +ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.17-G5.config,
  +ppc/ppc32/livecd-2.6.17-pegasos.config,
  +ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.17-power.config,
  +ppc/ppc32/livecd-2.6.17-ppc32.config:
  Imported the initial 2006.1 LiveCD kernel configs for Alpha and PPC. The
  Pegasos kernel config still does not work, and I'm still working on it.
  Import the correct 2006.1 PPC64 configs.

  01 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.15-G5.config,
  ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.15-power.config:
  Change CONFIG_TUN to a module on PPC64.

  31 Aug 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  alpha/installcd-2.4.30.config, alpha/installcd-2.6.15.1.config,
  hppa/installcd-2.6.16-hppa32.config, hppa/installcd-2.6.16-hppa64.config,
  ppc/ppc32/installcd-2.6.17-apple.config,
  sparc/sparc64/2.6.16-sparc64-generic.config,
  ppc/ppc32/installcd-2.6.17-pegasos.config,
  sparc/sparc64/2.6.17-sparc64-generic.config:
  Made CONFIG_BLK_DEV_MD=y on alpha/hppa/ppc32/ppc64/sparc for bug #112962.

  31 Aug 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +alpha/installcd-2.4.30.config, +ppc/ppc64/installcd-2.6.15-G5.config,
  +alpha/installcd-2.6.15.1.config,
  +sparc/sparc64/2.6.17-sparc64-generic.config,
